      "text": "Office Memorandum • UNITED STATES GOVERNMENT",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "TO : Director, FBI",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "text": "DATE: June 2, 1949",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "text": "FROM : SAC, New Orleans",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "SUBJECT: FLYING DISCS",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "Re SAC Letter 38, dated March 25, 1949 entitled as above.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "The Bureau is advised that through the Office of Naval Intelligence,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "New Orleans, Louisiana, this office has been advised that within the past ten",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "days three sightings of flying discs have been reported in the City of New Or-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "leans. The information seems to be that the single discs were in straight flight",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "and traveling in a general direction of North, in late afternoon about the size",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "of an observation plane, but the shape of a saucer. The Navy stated that two",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "witnesses have advised that the object was traveling end over end; that weather",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "conditions were good; that sightings were made outdoors by persons who did not",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "wear glasses; that the dates were May 18, 19 and 23, 1949. The Navy states",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "that it was possible these objects were weather balloons, but that these are",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "used from only one airport, released over an hour before the times of sighting",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "and would generally be out of sight in a few minutes.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "The above is being furnished the Bureau for future reference since",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "the Navy has informed that all three instances were investigated by the Army",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "Intelligence.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
